text.__SUMMARY__:
Cyperus cuspidatus is a sedge of the family Cyperaceae that is native to  Australia.The annual sedge typically grows to a height of 2.5 to 15 centimetres (0.98 to 5.91 in) and has a tufted habit. It blooms between February and August producing green-yellow-brown flowers.
It is found along creeks, streams and rivers in the Kimberley region of Western Australia where it grows in stony red sand-loam soils over sandstone.
